This paper is primarily focused on human activity understanding in videos, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and evaluation metrics, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multiple datasets and experiments, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.RO (Robotics).
